		{
			"type": "action",
			"name": "Wild Ride",
			"system": {
				"actionType": {
					"value": "reaction"
				},
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> the Púca is polymorphed as a rideable creature (usually a horse); <strong>Trigger</strong> the Púca is being ridden</p><hr /><p> the Púca may immediately Strides twice. After the Púca's Stride, the rider can no longer safely dismount until the Púca chooses to stop. Attempting to dismount while in motion requires a @Check[acrobatics|dc:15] Check or take @Damage[2d6[bludgeoning]] damage.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> the creature takes no damage and lands in a space within 5 feet from the Púca</p><p><strong>Success</strong> the creature takes half-damage and lands in a space within 5 feet from the Púca</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> the creature takes full damage and lands @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.j91X7x0XSomq8d60]{Prone} within 5 feet from the Púca</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> the creature takes full damage, is considered prone and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} by the Púca (CD 15 [[/act escape]]). Everytime the Púca Strides, the creature takes @Damage[2d6[bludgeoning]] damage (@Check[fortitude|dc:15|basic] Save) and is moved with the Púca, remaining grabbed. This is considered forced movement.</p>",
					"gm": ""
				},
